## Tiered Validation

Use fast feedback loops during development, full validation before PR.

### After Each Code Change (Tier 1 - Immediate)

**Solana (Anchor):**
```bash
anchor build  # Compile check
```

**EVM (Foundry):**
```bash
forge build  # Compile check
```

### After Completing a Feature/Fix (Tier 2 - Fast)

**Solana:**
```bash
anchor test  # Unit + integration tests
```

**EVM:**
```bash
forge test -vvv  # Tests with verbosity
```

### Before Creating PR (Tier 3 - Full, MANDATORY)

**Solana:**
```bash
anchor build
anchor test
cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings
cargo fmt --all -- --check
```

**EVM:**
```bash
forge build
forge test --fuzz-runs 1000
forge fmt --check
```

**DO NOT skip Tier 3 before PR.** Fast tiers are for iteration speed, not completeness.

## Security Checklists

### Solana Security (MANDATORY before PR)
- [ ] PDAs re-derived on-chain (never trust client)
- [ ] Account ownership verified
- [ ] Checked math everywhere
- [ ] Instruction data bounds validated
- [ ] Accounts closed properly (zero data + transfer lamports)
- [ ] Signer checks on all privileged operations

### EVM Security (MANDATORY before PR)
- [ ] ReentrancyGuard on state-changing externals
- [ ] Checks-effects-interactions pattern followed
- [ ] SafeERC20 for token transfers
- [ ] No tx.origin for auth
- [ ] Events emitted for all state changes
- [ ] Access control on privileged functions
- [ ] Slippage/deadline protection on swaps

